{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, neurons in the olfactory bulb respond to odorants in a spatially organized manner, creating what can be referred to as an \"olfactory map\" that the brain utilizes to identify distinct smells.",
    "The mechanism of combinatorial coding allows a single odor to activate multiple receptors, enhancing an individual's ability to differentiate between a nearly infinite number of odors.",
    "AI techniques can support the modeling of this complex process in two key ways.",
    "First, machine learning models can extract patterns from neuroimaging data by learning the spatial and temporal structure of neural activity.",
    "These methods help identify relationships between stimulus properties and brain responses, making it possible to infer how the brain encodes different odors."
  ]
}